Often I need to be working on a code that is indented by two spaces, however, it is really hard for me to work with code indented by two spaces. What I would like to be able to do is increase the indentation visually. Now I am not talking about replacing the two spaces with four spaces, but increasing the width of the space character when it's used as indentation. Basically render the width of all spaces at the beginning of a line with a respect to a predefined scale.
**An example:**
I have a file `index.js` with an indentation of 2 spaces.
```js
if (THIS_FEATURE_IS_IMPLEMENTED) {
  console.log('I am happy!');
} else {
  console.log('I am sad...');
}
```
After setting the scale of an indentation space to `2`, I would end up with the file **looking** like it is indented (but not actually) by four spaces.
```js
if (THIS_FEATURE_IS_IMPLEMENTED) {
    console.log('I am happy!');
} else {
    console.log('I am sad...');
}
```
Could work similarly to how the project tree indentation setting works.
I have not found any extension that I could accomplish this with. If there is such an extension, please let me know.
